Do you have the need for speed ?!?!  If so, you won't want to miss out on this hard to find, super low hour Baja 232 Islander.  Only 171.2 hours, fully loaded with a Mercruiser 7.4L MPI Bravo 1.  This bow-rider is in absolute pristine condition with snap out carpet, 8 person capacity, thru-hull exhaust, (so people know it's you :), Stereo CD player and stand-up bolster seating, 2 covers,  custom Heritage tandem axle trailer with spare!!

Known for its blend of sport and speed, the Baja 232 is equipped for peak performance. Like all Bajas, its deep-V hull was built to deliver a smooth ride even in rough water. It also offers options normally available only on larger boats, like textured deck surfaces, Kiekhaefer high-performance controls, and MerCruiser power up to 310 horsepower. The Baja 232 Islander is totally ideal for a weekend outing as it is for high-performance speed.

A fiberglass cockpit floor liner offers comfortable traction and makes cleanup easy at the end of a fun day on the water.  This is an amazing family fun machine!

1998 Sweetwater SW180ES 18 foot float boat Pontoon Boat.
It floats! It has been left out in the weather for at least 2 years before acquired property on Buckeye Lake.
I now have clean titles, 1st title for watercraft and 2nd title for motor.
Project boat. Likely needs new trimming and seats, and cleaning.
Don't know if motor works. I think it obviously needs rehaul/retooling, left out in yearly rain/snow. Still attached to and installed in watercraft. Selling both together as one package.

This is a project for someone. It can stay there until there's a decent offer accepted. Compare to new 2021 Sweetwaters: $35-55K plus tax, watercraft and outboard motor. Compare to used 1990s/2000s Sweetwaters, at 6,000-14,000 plus tax.
Price above is paid to seller. Can meet at bank for safe transfer of cash vs boat title and motor title.
No mailed cashier checks or scams. Call or text with questions.
You then will also owe watercraft/motor sales tax to Ohio when you present the titles with a small Ohio title fee.

This is a super-fast super light tandem that is great for a pair of paddlers that want to race, fast touring, and day-tripping and does not want to deal with the weight and bulkiness of a typical tandem boat. The Stellar 21' Tandem (ST21) Sea Kayak has long, efficient hull lines that will slice through the water. With a narrow catch and our durable, yet lightweight laminates, the ST21 is at home for racing as it is in on long tours quickly eating the miles. 2 storage hatches and 3 bulkheads provide ample storage and stiffness and an over stern rudder helps with steering in challenging conditions. A full 3 point foot brace provides you with a stable platform for a strong leg drive, while a formed seat pad and thigh brace provide comfort and stability when it gets rough.

Alumacraft Quetico 185 CL Canoe is 18 ft 5 in long with 37 in beam and 4 persons or 795 lb persons, gear load capacity. Ser. No. ACBS0230L294. A Motorguide Stealth 2000V 40 lb thrust motor and detachable motor mount is included with two paddles.

I've paddled this solo with a pair of doodles around our lake and used it with a drop-in rowing rig (see separate listing). Test paddling encouraged. I've never used the motor since they're not permitted on our lake.

Good initial stability, excellent secondary. 33.5‚Äù at the waterline & 37‚Äù max with some tumblehome to keep the gunwales close. Fast. A knot faster than a Grumman 18 & 1/2 knot slower than a Wenonah Minnesota II. If you are driving hard and flat... she tracks so well, you'd think she would not turn. A keel, but a bit of rocker too. But, heel her over a bit on a cheek and she turns in her own length. I did two 90's, left, then right to follow the current around a rock ledge, she turned like 13-foot solo canoe.

When she plunged through a series of 2+ foot tall rapids, the bow shape punched the crests to the side... as long as I held dead straight the only water to enter was that taller than the bow. 13.5 inch center depth stayed bone dry.
A good craft - 71 pounds, so not a light weight, but not horrible.
Hauls a heavy load with ease. Deals with wind and waves easily. Great lake boat. A fine family canoe!

Boating season is here and boy, this is a complete boating package. We are selling a brand new, never used Zodiac 270 Aero inflatable along with a Tohatsu 4 HP outboard engine.

The 8'8"" Zodiac is perfect to use as a dinghy for your large boat. It is also great for fishing or just gunkholing. The Zodiac comes with 2 oars, 1 seat, a foot pump, repair kit and instructions.  We are also including a Airhead high volume electric pump for speedy filling of the boat and 2 never used life vests.
The 4 HP Tohatsu outboard comes with an additional external fuel tank for extra time on the water. The Tohatsu was the only 4 HP motor we could find with an external fuel tank.
When you come to pick up your prize follow my instructions or you will not go to the right entrance. DO NOT TRUST YOUR GPS!

Ready to sail or cruise, partially refit and well maintained.  Needs a few things and a little love.  The upgraded, Universal Atomic 4, gas powered 30 horsepower engine is strong, and always starts on the first or second try. It has a refrigerator/icebox, and a 2 burner stove/oven.  Recent toilet and plumbing throughout, with electric pressure pump.  Good main and self-furling genoa.  Epoxy primer on scraped hull a few years ago.  Running rigging aging, but sturdy.  Set up for solar with three batt banks (need new batts), I have replaced each thing as necessary including most of the upholstery on cushions and cabin walls.  She is showing her age, but will provide years more of fun for someone.  I don't have the time to finish the project.  Some upcoming projects include:  purchase and install new sailing instruments and depth finder in old positions. SS Radio and Stereo included but need to be hooked up.  Custom cover needs zipper repair, otherwise in good shape. Most Recent trip was from New Buffalo to Montrose Harbor.   On the hard in Waukegan, IL.  Includes spring launch!   Make an offer for this AS-IS Sale.

20' Pontoon on brand new tandem axle trailer - $11,000 (Mt Carmel east side of cincinnati)
QR Code Link to This Post
$11000.00 cash and this is a long desriptive ad but if you're serious about buying a boat then this is the kind of ad you should be reading.
If you see this ad, yes the pontoon is still for sale so please don't ask that.

There is some minor general maintenance that I was going to do to the motor but have decided to let the new owner do that. I have the parts, (thermostat, spark plugs, water pump impeller.) The motor runs great but the cables (shift - throttle) needs adjusted. These are all normal things that SHOULD be done regularly. They in no way are keeping this motor from the water, I just play it safe every year.

Also, please do the math here. My price is $11k. I do not have this pontoon over priced. PLEASE do not ask me to accept a low ball amount. You will find other pontoons needing work and mostly without a trailer or the trailer is junk but this pontoon is completely redone from the cross members up. You can take this pontoon anywhere and be confident you'll have a great time.
I have done all the hard work and made this boat new again. You absolutely will not find another pontoon like this for this price.

1986 Palm Beach 20' pontoon with a Evinrude 50hp. I just rebuilt this pontoon this past summer because I planned on keeping it for the next 10 years but now my wife wants a camper and I dont have room for both.

I replaced the old factory 1/2"" floor with 3/4"" premium marine grade plywood. I sealed it on both sides and used all stainless hardware. Brand new 32oz rubber backed premium plush carpet glued and sealed. I extended the fencing to the deck length. Replaced the old nasty fishing seats with nice new premium bench seats with lean backs. New captains chair. New stainless steering wheel. New waterproof marine stereo with 6 great sounding waterproof marine speakers. Brand new led lights for headlights, water line lights, deck lights and navigation lights. Nice new stainless steel ""LOUD"" horn. Nice 8' tall bimini top matches the carpet color and covers half the deck. The front of the boat has a nice flip down stainless steel telescopic boarding ladder. New automatic with remote anchor winch with 100' rope so no more pulling an anchor up by hand. Let your woman be a real princess in this pontoon. This pontoon is new from the cross members up. The motor runs great too but is not original to the boat. The boat had a 28spl which just wasn't enough. The motor is untitled. I bought it from a guy in Ky. and they do not title motors there. I did get a BOS from him but apparently it had to be notorized and we didn't know that so Ohio bmv wont accept the BOS. Most people could care less about a motor title but some do so....there ya go.

The pontoon also comes with a nice full waterproof cover. The pontoon sits on a BRAND NEW Yacht Club tandem axle trailer with surge brakes and guides and has a nice boarding ladder built in. The trailer alone was $3500 and came from Allcraft Marine on Kellogg Ave.
2 brand new batteries with new selector switch. 12 gallon removable fuel tank. The boat is titled as a 20' but the toons are actually 21' due to the nose cones.

Please text me first, my phone marks everyone not in the contacts as scam likely. All communication after 1st text will be by actually talking to each other. If you can't get on board with that, please don't waste my time. No emails, those all go to my spam.

This lightly used MacGregor sailboat features a water ballast system that makes the boat lightweight for trailering and a rudder and centerboard that retract completely so it sits very low on its trailer making it possible to be launched at any ramp. After the boat is launched a valve inside the boat is opened and a water tank in the bottom of the hull is gravity-filled with 1200 lbs. of water. The valve is then closed, trapping the water. Under power or sail, the 1200 lbs. make the boat stable and self-righting. When the boat is floated back on its trailer, the valve is opened and the water starts to drain out of the boat, leaving a trailering package that is lighter than most small powerboats. One person can raise the mast, launch the boat and sail away in 15 minutes.

‚Ä¢ Main sail, Genoa, Jib each with a sail bag
‚Ä¢ Trailer with built-in boarding ladder for easy access

The 2001 VLX is a boat that has an exceptional wake right out of the box. Great for Wakesurfing or Wakeboarding.  The 500-pound MLS system bumps it up to world class. Riders will weight it how they want to. It has tons of storage space for weighting options. The wake is wide, with a smooth transition- the kind you can change from the flats. There are two detachable ballast in rear hatches. Along with a center ballast and storage. All controlled with dash switches. Perfect pass for individual speed settings.  Depth finderHas power wedge for more added wake dimension. I have owned this boat for 4 years.  I am the second owner. Great boat for fishing the Great Lakes and the Ohio River!  Rare Regal 250 Royal LF made for fishing and cruising. The boat is 25 ft long and has an 8 ft beam. Its large cockpit area has a non skid fiberglass floor and plenty of room to move about while fishing.  This is a very deep boat and would do well in the Great Lakes.  Lots of storage.  Live well. The Cuddy is large enough to accommodate 2 adults and includes a separate enclosed head. The gelcoat still shines. The floor appears solid as does transom. Powered by OMC Cobra 5.7L 260 hp sterndrive.  It has a newer custom cockpit cover.  Included is a 2008 Venture aluminum I beam trailer with a 6425 lb capacity. The trailer alone is worth at least 2500!  Average NADA retail for this package is over $7000.

Mechanically sound cruiser.  There's some work to be done to this roomy classic cabin cruiser, but lots has been accomplished.   It is 10 ft. 4 in. wide and 28 feet long.  Powered by newer Mercruiser 5.7L 255hp motor with low hours and Mercruiser outdrive.  The boat has a complete camper canvas and a cockpit cover.  The motor and outdrive are worth much more than the asking price.  The Mariner has been one of Carver's more popular models.  It has a lot of room in its cabin area. This particular boat has a fiberglass hull and wood with nautilex vinyl covering on its bow and decks.  Options include an electric head, freshwater system, cooktop, canvas, large teak swim platform.  It has a full cockpit cover and camper canvas.  The boat has been professionally rewired with a new power panel.  Its fiberglass hull is in great condition
column2: however, all the old wood decking has been removed and is in the process of being replaced.  The boat operated fine and was winterized prior to current project.   Looking for someone interested in finishing the restoration. Boat is located at Mariner's Landing Marina.  It does not have a trailer.   Open to reasonable offers.

14 ft very wide and very very stable boat. I've had it in the Tennessee River many times, Alabama and mainly Ohio and it's as stable as can be. Runs about 25 mph with 2 fat dudes and gear! Motorcycle fires up 2nd or 3rd pull religiously and runs amazing. Not pressed to sell and will entertain trade offers just depends what you offer! It's hard to find mercury motors in this condition up for grabs these days! Price negotiable to a point. I absolutely love the boat so again not super pressed to sell. Price may seem high but breaking it down helps, finding a perfect running 25 motor is a couple grand+, finding a nice wide flat bottom is gonna be a couple grand +, then anchors, fish finder, safyey gear, lights and everything else adds up quickly so finding a perfect catfish setup ready for water is today makes it easier! I literally had it on Tennessee River Friday and Saturday catching fish!

Trailer, Powered by a 5.0L MPI 260 HP MerCruiser, Bravo 3 Drive and only 469 Hrs. This Boat Looks Very Sharp, the Gel Coat has a nice Shine and the Bottom Paint looks Very Good. Step On Board and the Cockpit is impressive in size for a 24 foot boat, with a Large Aft Bench, Beautiful Wood Table and Wet Bar. The Drives Seat is Comfortable for 2 and has a Flip Up Bolster for added Visibility. The Port Side Companion Seats Certainly make this boat different from others and the design is great for entertaining. Molded in Steps take you through the walk through windshield and the Bow is Very Flat with Non Skid Deck Surfaces. Walk into the Cabin and this Pocket Cruiser Comes to Life, with good head room, a Full Forward Dinette that can Convert into a Berth, Very Nice Galley and a Mid Cabin for additional Guest. The Head is all Fiberglass Lines and can be used as a Shower as well. Over all this boat should impress inside and out!

17' Grumman square stern canoe with 35 lbs thrust Minnkota trolling motor, life jackets, cushioned seats with backs, and paddles. I bought this canoe years ago in Wisconsin where it was used only on a lake. It has the heavier gage aluminum hull. It is in near perfect condition and the bottom has no dents. It's wired with 4 gage wire so the battery can sit near the bow if the trolling motor is used. It has teak transom plates both inside and out. Rated for 5HP motor, 860 lbs. capacity. There is no battery for the trolling motor.
The canoe is located in West Lafayette.

Please respond by email or phone only. I can't respond to texts because of spam. Thanks.

This 1965 Chris Craft is one of 60 ‚Äì 17‚Äô Custom Ski built in 1965, and one of 150 Custom Ski hulls built between 1965 and 1967. The boat is ready to run as-is, or would make a great candidate for complete restoration to mint original condition. Cover and trailer are included with full price purchase.

I've owned this 1980 Catalina 25 for the last 10 years and it has spent almost the entire time on the trailer.  Only dunked in the lake maybe 12 times for day sails, then put right back on the trailer.  I'll be 100% honest regarding its condition.
Trailer - The brakes and surge coupler were changed 8 years ago.  Goodyear Endurance tires new in 2020 and I just serviced the bearings.
Outboard - Tohatsu 9.9hp 4 stroke with 25"" shaft.  It is 8 years old with probably 10 hours on it.  It is essentially brand new still.

Boat - This is a swing keel model with a tall rig mast.  The cabin has the pop-top for extra headroom.  The interior has a full set of cushions and are in good shape.  The boat has a new electrical panel, but only 2 interior lights work.  Also comes with a navy blue bimini that is in almost new condition, but the cover shows a little wear due to outdoor elements.

Sails - The loose-foot main sail is in great shape (still crispy).  A previous owner had it re-cut to raise the boom and allow more cockpit headroom.  The 110% jib is still in good condition, but had a small hole that I patched with sail tape.  The jib sheets are brand new.
The boat overall still has a lot of life left in it, but it needs a better home where it will be used.  The keel doesn't have any slop or keel knock with the pivot pin.

The boat needs an epoxy primer and paint on the deck and below the waterline.  It appears that a previous owner painted the topsides a long time ago and has some scratches.  Also, the cockpit floor is a little soft.  Nothing that has to be remedied immediately, but within the next few years.
Most of the expensive pieces on the boat are near new condition.  It just needs a little time and energy to make it shine again.

1998 SeaRay 175 I/O speedboat runs great.  I bought it last June as we were planning some lake vacations over the summer as a great way to keep 3 teens and their friends outside and entertained.  Had it out on the water 2 weekends in Michigan and a 3-week vacation in Minnesota.  Pulled 3 tubes for hours and hours every day with no problems... tons of fun!  Also did some skiing and knee-boarding.  Trailer has new tires as of summer 2020.  1600-mile round trip to Minnesota and back with no troubles.  Boat also includes a nice towable cover.

When I was looking for a boat last year, this is the only one in my price range where the owner would take it out on the water with me.  I didn't want to buy a boat without being able to have it on the water first.  The boat is not cosmetically perfect, but it runs great... and that's what was most important to me... I wanted to make sure it was going to do it's job - and it did great!

This boat is in  good condition in all respects and has been very well kept. It has always been used on freshwater.   This boat is set up with a fixed winged keel and swing down center board.  The Center board will need a bit of attention but can easily be sailed without it.    This will come with a nearly new Mercury Long Shaft 9.9 HP Motor with electric start. The motor was purchase brand new in 2017 and has less than 30 hours on it.  That cost alone was about $3000.    The sails,  winches, hardware etc. are all good to go.  Mainsail, Jib and the Spinnaker are in good condition.    This complete boat, motor, trailer, sails and and related hardware is $4950 on a pick up basis near Redfield SD.   A meeting or delivery might be possible.   If you do not need the motor the price is only $2500.  Please use the CL Messaging service for further contact information.   Thanks for looking and lets hope summer is right around the corner!

Humminbird 597 ciHD down imaging sonar. Custom built decking with storage underneath. 3 Cabelas deep cycle heavy duty marine batteries, one for motor, sonar and lights, 2 for trolling motor. Night compliant fishing lights. This has been an amazing boat and nothing is wrong with it, I just dont have time to fish anymore due to work schedual. Original owner of the outboard, trolling motor, batteries and sonar. Asking $5500 negotiable. Text ONLY @ 402-Six eight one-4897.

1985 Supra Ski boat with 351 Ford V8 engine, carbureted with electronic ignition. Includes trailer and fly-high pole for skiers/wake boarders!!  I purchased this ski boat back at the end of 2013, at that time the hour meter was showing 55 hours (obviously it has been replaced so I am unsure of the total ""actual"" hours on the boat).  I can't tell you how many owners the boat has had but I know the gentlemen who owned it before me took good care of it and so did I.  The previous owner re-upholstered seats, rebuilt the transmission (I still have the original, comes with sale), added an electronic lift pump and had most everything working well on the boat.  I fixed what was not working when I purchased the machine (trailer lights, instrument panel lighting and various other items) and I've had great luck with it on the water. Trailer tires are in great shape, one is only 2 years old, probably has less than 50 miles on it. It has a depth finder, great stereo and sound system, accent lighting and it starts and runs well, PLENTY of power and the engine sounds great.  This is the type of boat that you treat with fuel stabilizer in the fall, put a light charge on the battery in the spring and it starts right up.  I've only been left on the water twice and a new starter cured that problem.  The only reason I'm selling it is to acquire something larger for the lake we live near.  I will entertain offers but I will not sell this to anyone that is not willing to talk to me on the phone.  Texts are fine if you have questions but we will have to talk on the phone at some point so if you refuse to do that I will assume you are a scammer...  scammers please don't waste my time!!!  Please call 402-990-eight six three two if you are interested. Thanks for looking!

Gotta go! Rare model Saltare.  It was Supra top of the line 5000 series in 1995.  24ft with 5.8l PCM.  Runs amazing.  New custom interior 3yrs ago.  Stereo Jams.  Fosgate tower speakers, 3 amps.  Big Air Tower.  New floor 1 month ago.  New alternator 1 weeks ago.  New impeller recently and have a backup for you.  Replaced belts with new alternator.  I do all my own winterizing every year and change the tranny and oil before every season.  Dual axel trailer with bearing buddy and all lights working.  I drove this boat from Texas 5yrs ago.  The hour meter broke about a month ago on 985.  Probably added 20hrs since then.  I got 5k in custom interior, 4k in stereo install, $500 for the new floor and $800 in the tower.
I started to swap out the switch panel and never finished.  You will need to finish as I got in over my head. :)
There is a slight oil leak which I cannot find anywhere but some oil ends up in the water in the engine basin.

Because of the switch panel swap I have not had my 2 bilge pumps or the vent air for months.  Still drive the boat everyday just need to lift the engine cover from time to time when starting and when cruising
There is a small gouge in the front hull which has been there since I bought the boat.  Does not effect performance in any way.
When the hour meter failed the alarm would not stop so I snipped that wire.  Up to you to reconnect.
I am getting a new boat this week so she has to go.
